description.narrative: By 2016, 45,000 children aged 0-5 years particularly the most vulnerable, are benefiting from services following development norms and standards as well as from early learning and stimulation programs in selected areas., which contributes to Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2016, girls and boys aged 0-14 years in the three poorest quintiles benefit from education policies to ensure equitable access to quality basic education and opportunities for early childhood development.
